ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa GCIS JOHANNESBURG - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa says he feels secure in his position within the party. Ramaphosa says if the ANC is unhappy with him, he will gladly do what a disciplined member of the party will do and move on. WATCH: In conversation with ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa "Should members of the ANC say, no, you are not serving us well and you must move out, gladly so because I am a disciplined member of the African National Congress," he siad. The President has faced criticism from some party members over what they say is his failure to implement radical party resolutions.